# dbt Core / SQL Conventions

> **This rule covers dbt Core on Databricks** (Exodus Foundation, ironlayer_infra, client templates).
> For dbt Cloud Enterprise client engagements, see `dbt-cloud.mdc` instead.
> **For SQLMesh projects** (clients using SQLMesh as their transformation framework), see `sqlmesh.mdc` and use the `exodus-sqlmesh` Claude skill.

---

## dbt MCP Local Tools (available in Cursor via `dbt` MCP server)

These tools run against the local dbt project set by `DBT_PROJECT_DIR` in `~/.exodus/env.local`:

### CLI Tools
```
dbt_run             — Run one or more models against the dev warehouse
dbt_build           — Run + test models in DAG order
dbt_test            — Run tests on selected models
dbt_compile         — Compile models to SQL without executing (fast validation)
dbt_list            — List models matching a selector (e.g., +stg_coinbase__candles+)
dbt_parse           — Parse the project for syntax errors
dbt_show            — Preview first N rows of a model
dbt_source_freshness — Check all source freshness against warn/error thresholds
```

### Metadata Tools (no warehouse required)
```
get_all_models      — List all models with layer, materialization, schema
get_model_details   — Schema, columns, tests, config for a specific model
get_lineage         — Upstream/downstream DAG for a model
get_model_health    — Test pass/fail and freshness for a model
get_all_sources     — All sources with freshness config
get_exposures       — Downstream consumers of models
```

### Codegen Tools (requires `DISABLE_DBT_CODEGEN=false` in MCP env, already set)
```
generate_staging_model  — Generate a staging model SQL file from a source table
generate_model_yaml     — Generate a YAML companion file for an existing model
generate_source         — Generate a sources.yml block from a database table
```

**Prefer codegen tools** over manually writing boilerplate. Example workflow:
```
1. Use generate_source to scaffold sources.yml for a new raw table
2. Use generate_staging_model to scaffold the staging SQL
3. Use generate_model_yaml to add YAML companion with column descriptions
4. Manually add business logic and tests on top of the generated base
```

