## Model Naming (Medallion Architecture)

| Layer | Pattern | Materialization | Schema |
|---|---|---|---|
| Staging | `stg_{source}__{table}` | view | silver |
| Intermediate | `int_{domain}__{description}` | table | silver |
| Dimensions | `dim_{entity}` | incremental (merge) | gold |
| Facts | `fct_{event}` | incremental (merge) | gold |

Examples: `stg_coinbase__candles`, `int_crypto__daily_ohlcv`, `dim_asset`, `fct_trade`

## SQL Style

```sql
with

source as (
    select * from {{ source('bronze', 'raw_coinbase_candles') }}
),

cleaned as (

    select
        -- surrogate key: never MD5() directly
        {{ surrogate_key(['product_id', 'start_time']) }} as candle_id,
        product_id,
        lower(side)                                        as side,
        open::decimal(18, 8)                               as open_price,
        high::decimal(18, 8)                               as high_price,
        low::decimal(18, 8)                                as low_price,
        close::decimal(18, 8)                              as close_price,
        volume::decimal(24, 8)                             as volume,
        to_timestamp(start_time)                           as candle_at,
        current_timestamp()                                as _dbt_loaded_at

    from source
    where start_time is not null

)

select * from cleaned
```

## SQL Rules

- UPPERCASE all SQL keywords (`SELECT`, `FROM`, `WHERE`, `JOIN`, `WITH`, `AS`)
- CTE pattern: `with source as (...), cleaned as (...) select * from cleaned`
- Indent 4 spaces
- One column per line in `SELECT`
- Alias all columns explicitly — no `select *` in marts
- Max line length: 120 characters

## Required Macros

```sql
-- Surrogate key (never raw MD5)
{{ surrogate_key(['col1', 'col2']) }}

-- Safe division (never raw /)
{{ safe_divide(numerator, denominator) }}

-- PII masking (gold layer)
{{ pii_mask(email, 'email') }}

-- Audit columns (add to all models)
{{ audit_columns() }}  -- adds _dbt_loaded_at, _dbt_updated_at
```

## YAML Schema (required for every model)

```yaml
models:
  - name: stg_coinbase__candles
    description: "One row per OHLCV candle from Coinbase Advanced Trade API"
    config:
      materialized: view
      schema: silver
    columns:
      - name: candle_id
        description: "Surrogate key (product_id + start_time)"
        tests:
          - unique
          - not_null
      - name: open_price
        description: "Opening price in USD"
        tests:
          - not_null
          - positive_value

sources:
  - name: bronze
    database: "{{ env_var('DBT_CATALOG') }}_raw"
    schema: coinbase
    tables:
      - name: raw_coinbase_candles
        loaded_at_field: _extracted_at
        freshness:
          warn_after: { count: 6, period: hour }
          error_after: { count: 24, period: hour }
```

## Incremental Models (dims and facts)

```sql
{{ config(
    materialized='incremental',
    unique_key='candle_id',
    incremental_strategy='merge',
    on_schema_change='sync_all_columns',
) }}

{% if is_incremental() %}
where candle_at > (select max(candle_at) from {{ this }})
{% endif %}
```

## IronLayer Plan Integration

Before running dbt in CI, always run `ironlayer plan`:
- Validates the execution graph
- Reports cost estimate for the run
- Flags risky operations (full refresh, schema change)
- Only proceed if confidence ≥ 70% and zero BLOCK findings

## Source Freshness

Run `dbt source freshness` daily. Alert if:
- Bronze tables: warn > 6 hours stale, error > 24 hours
- Silver/Gold: warn > 12 hours, error > 48 hours
